They would have to run tests. That was the extent of my phone call with this vet. < text>
In 2016, I brought my first kitten in and purchased the kitten package (which I can not remember how much it was then) and had a great experience, no problems. Fast forward to this year, we decided to take in a 7 week old kitten (Charles) and decided to bring him here since we had a great experience. I purchased the kitten package which was $510. The first problem we encountered was he had diarrhea which we thought was normal due to the vaccinations. However, after the 3rd day we decided to call the doctor and ask if this was normal and they told us to bring him back in. I had to pay an additional charge for the visit and medication for his diarrhea. That night we noticed live tape worms in his diarrhea so I called the doctor back and they told me to bring him in immediately to get an injection which was more money that I paid for. Two days later, Charles had a follow up for his diarrhea which I had to pay for another visit. My husband then had to argue with the doctor for 30 minutes to give him antibiotics which helped with the diarrhea. Now, we are being forced out and they are refunding us only 20% of the kitten package that I paid for and gave me attitude while doing so. With the refund of the package I have probably paid well over $400 in the two and half weeks that I've had Charles. We have to find a vet that will take in Charles with only one set of vaccinations. I am very disappointed in the service. All I wanted was to give Charles a good home and he's had such a horrible experience. Good luck if you choose this place for your pet. I recommend anywhere but here.< /text>

< review>
Wow, just left this horrible place. First, my dog has a sensitive stomach so vet visits are common unfortunately. My vet was unable to schedule anything until next week. So rather than walk in and possibly wait several hours. I called around to see if another vet had an appointment available for today. I live 5 minutes from the office being reviewed and was told to come on in.

After waiting in the car (Covid 19 precautions) for approximately 30 minutes, they finally came and took my dog. About an hour later they call me and say they wanted to xray and do other "treatments" and gave me a price of $1100. Here's the issue, my dog has a history of stomach issues and just 3 months ago we were at a 24 hour emergency vet with the same symptoms. The 24 hr ER vet offering the same treatments (xray, blood work, meds, etc) charged me half of what Monterey Park was trying to charge me. "How is this possible?" I asked. They responded with, "different vets charge different amounts". Well on this basis, an office open at normal business hours with a customer who made an appointment is charging more than a 24 hour ER vet (I walked into the ER at 2:00am). I would highly recommend that people go elsewhere because they are clearly too expensive.

Lastly, after questioning the price and removing items I felt were unnecessary they still charged me $400 for blood work. Not only that but their attitudes completely changed. They came out and charged my card. Another hour later and they brought my dog. He jumped in the car and they handed me a receipt.  The woman closed my car door and walked away. No information about the blood work or anything. No advice on other things to do as any other vet we've seen would do. Nothing. I assume the blood work will take time but the ER vet had results in under an hour. < user_name>
Josh W.</user_name>
< Review>
So I ran out of Coffeemate creamer, which is a problem for my morning routine, but I'm reluctant to go to the trouble of running to Target or Albertson's for just creamer. But on the way to the Credit Union I noticed Knolls Market and thought I'd see if they have any Coffeemate. EUREKA! They have it, and in my favorite flavor, and in a good sized jug, not the mini-me version like over at the Waalew gas mart. So I take it up to the counter, the gent rings me up, but when it comes to the credit card processing, he complains about the machine running slow and jokes that if it fails on him again he might start cursing at it. I respond that I know the frustration of tech messing with you. I don't know if it was just friendly conversation, or a distraction, or setting up an alibi. But when I checked my credit card statement he had charged me over $11 for the Coffeemate! The usual price is around $3. I don't believe $11 is Knolls Market's actual price for the creamer. Either the guy goofed and keyed it in wrong by accident (hopefully), or he thought I was too distracted to notice the overcharge, or too rich to miss the money. Well, I noticed, and I'm broke, so being overcharged by $8 is like a sock in the gut. If the owner concedes the error and offers to re-credit my card for the difference, this review will disappear. Until then, I'll feel that I've been robbed. I don't know if he's the owner, but the clerk was a larger guy, bushy brown hair, and a modest beard. Always ask for a receipt and make sure you were charged properly! My purchase was on 3/24/21, probably around 10-11am, and the total was $11.53. Maybe the owner can look up that transaction and verify my story. 1 star above the minimum accounts for them having the Coffemate I needed and being my caffeine savior that morning.<//Review>

Before I start it is so important to know that this dental office is open now and serving all types of needs. They take every precaution and enforce social distancing. You can be confident your safety is their first priority.

Dr. Huss,
Thank you for your team. This group of people truly define what it means to be a team. I haven‚Äôt been the most pleasant patient to deal with on several occasions due to discomfort and bone spurs. What truly sets you all apart is that you all handled it with care and compassion and at the end of each visit I felt grateful for having went. I even had work done by you on one occasion and that speaks a ton for your character as a leader. Thank you.

Dr. Castillo,
This is arguably one of the most patient guys I‚Äôve ever encountered. Although, I have not had but one visit with him I look forward to getting my teeth and gums back in order. He is an outstanding member of your team and I appreciate the approach he takes with patients. Thank you Dr. Castillo.

Dr. Yafai,
He is the Oral Surgeon here and this guys is a next level black belt when it comes to what he does. He remembers you even after first meeting you a month prior. Impressive. He is very good at what he does. I had a tooth extracted and could‚Äôve fallen asleep on the table during the process. It was really the best extraction I could‚Äôve hoped for. The staff who have seen my mouth since his visit have all said how well the site healed over and that is a small testament to his work. Thank you.

Sahar F. is one of the Registered Dental Hygienists at Moorpark Dental Group. I had my first visit with her 6/25. We started the visit by me expressing my ridiculous fear of dentists. She handled that in a way that immediately made my worries vanish. Her witty reply instantly changed my mind toward the positive. Go ahead, book an appointment yourself and call her a Dentist. You‚Äôll see. Throughout the appointment I continued to be impressed by her precision, her control and her ability to continuously ease my mind in an uncomfortable situation.
At one point and several times thereafter I even noticed her sharpen her various precision dental picks. Let me tell you why this matters. Sharpening any instrument is a skill that is acquired and in order to be successful at it you must practice an awful lot. Many professionals will ship this task out to others, but the ones that take the time to develop this skill themselves are exceptional when using their instruments to perform their craft. You can tell the difference immediately. Sahar, Thank you for being an amazing example of a true professional. Your service based heart and the way you care for yourself is reflected In the way you treat your patients. I highly recommend you book that next deep cleaning with her. You will not regret this.

Last but certainly not least, Miguelina.  Miguelina, is an amazing asset to this team as well. She is always concerned for your comfort and wellbeing as a patient and has an amazing memory. I promise, you will feel like she knows every single persons name who goes through that doorway. You will feel welcomed and like a VIP every time you encounter her. First impressions of a place often tend to be flat and generic. The bar for what to expect from a Dental office was definitely raised as a result of her. I wish you guys nothing but success for many years to come. Thank you for all you have done and will do for me.

AM.<//Text>

110328310416450554336< /userid>
<review>BUYER BEWARE--They bait and switch you from an offer too good to be true, for a plan so expensive, you'll need financing or to break into your emergency savings to pay for it.

I moved to Moorpark  in 2015 and was way overdue for my routine six-month cleaning and check-up, but since this has been an aberration in my overall adult life of dental healthcare maintenance, I was surprised with the first-time new-patient examination findings.

I went to the clinic thinking this was a great deal--an exam, x-rays, and a cleaning for a low price of $59.00.   Their disclaimer that you only get the cleaning if you don't have periodontal disease didn't concern me, as I was confident that didn't apply to me.   A simple ordinary tell-tale sign is my gums don't bleed when I floss, which is daily, no less than once a day, though often more often, to remove any food stuck between my teeth.

The x-rays were a cheap quality and type, and several of the tooth images didn't come out and so the technician kept repeating them, giving me more radiation exposure each time, and until I realized this was a chronic issue with either the machine or the software.   At first I was very cooperative and flexible.  But when it became several times where the machine wouldn't perform, I lost faith in the equipment they were using and in their process.

Then I got the exam from the dentist, who was very cordial and friendly and made great small talk.   He said all my crowns, and fillings looked fine.   He told me what I knew, about my receding gum lines, something I was aware of and have always been told can be managed with good oral hygiene and diet.  But then he told me the bad news.   I had severe periodontal disease so I couldn't get the cleaning I had come in to receive.   The dentist said I needed laser cleaning and resurfacing  or planing, or something like that--a procedure that would cost me thousands of dollars.    Then then handed me off to their financing and scheduling plan coordinator.

I was upset and said thanks but no thanks and I got a second opinion from another dentist in town.

I needed a cleaning, and I welcomed a real exam and set of x-rays that were clear and complete.

It is my personal opinion that Moorpark Dental Group and Orthodontics is a scam.  I feel I got ripped-off  with their bait and switch from an offer for a very inexpensive exam, x-rays and a cleaning for a price too good to be true, to reel me into a very expensive and questionable treatment I didn't want or need.

BUYER BEWARE!   If they tell you you need their laser treatment for periodontal disease, hold onto your wallet and go get a second opinion.  I feel really ripped off.   I want my money back.</review>< rate>
1</rate>

Then, of all the people I met that morning for my MRI schedule, I completely forgot the person did my MRI on July 7, 2018, this guy I must commend, such a nice and very professional individual. < Review>
Never go to this company!
After I had an MRI, gave them my insurance info and paid, they made an error of some sort and failed to keep track of the fact I'd paid them and they incorrectly took down my Blue Shield info and rather than contacting me or the insurance company to figure out what had happened they just sent debt collectors ('CMRE FSI') after me - asking for what the price would have been if I hadn't had insurance >$1,000. Once I figured out what had happened I contacted Health Diagnostics and my insurance - the woman I spoke with at Health Diagnostics assured me they would call the debt collectors off and would write me a letter so I could contest this hit to my otherwise great credit score. Weeks - nay - months later I'm still getting contacted by the same debt collection agency, and I never got a letter explaining what had happened so I can contest this on my credit report. Don't go here unless you'd like this horrible situation, and continual harassment from debt collectors to be your reality. Health Diagnostics you are the worst and I'm not done with you.< /Review>

I ordered online with Ace Hardware, who delivers to this store. Due to the circumstances of the moment, I was unable to get to the store within the time frame for pickup (5 days). Or hold on to it. However, the manager was completely unhelpful in telling me whether it was in stock, and just said that it was the policy. <user_name>Andrew Copert<//user_name><Text>I used to live just across the Panhandle from Cole Hardware's original location on Cole in SF and they were my go-to when I had a project around the apartment so was happy to see them expand across the Bay to Rockridge (I think they were stalking me).

Friendly and knowledgeable staff. Pretty good selection of goods. They will special order stuff that they don't have in stock.

If you need a specialty tool for just one use ask about their tool lending service. I found out about this when I was guessing at the size of the shower valve wrench I'd need and the guy helping me asked me if this was for a project or something I'd need long term for multiple uses.

Parking can be difficult, but they are near BART, if you can easily carry what you're going to buy.</Text>< Pics>

<username>Rob Stephenson< /username><Date>1619711959546< /Date>< rating>

<Review>I pulled up to this place since we were looking for some seafood. Loved the look and vibe of the outside and inside. We talked about having a party there just based on the looks.  The service was quick and friendly. These are the 2 stars I gave them.
We ended up ordering the same thing, as we were both craving seafood. The ‚ÄúBig Baja Bucket‚Äù. It comes with lobster,shrimp, chicken, skirt steak, corn on the cob, beans, rice, and flour tortillas.
Unfortunately when the food arrived we were very disappointed. It had smaller than I would expect seafood portions. That‚Äôs not a deal breaker, as long as it‚Äôs done well. It was not. The shrimp and lobster were overcooked, rubber. The chicken was so salty, it was inedible. The skirt steak was ok, and the corn was dry and tasteless. She had Mexican style corn and I had the grilled. Both tasteless. I looked over and noticed my date was only eating the corn, the ‚Äúbest item in the bowl. Even the rice and beans were boring. Liked the tortillas and sauces.
Normally I would try to go back a second time to see if they were just have an very off night. That will not be the case this time.
Really wanted to like this place.</Review><pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipMNaXrOo63uKZE7tdUpPwcGw9NqdS6VEiMgL9l8=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP2oiegyXuiUI_uza7bjqMCYCmbJW3yhbOjPi2e=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNqyqJ44jmQomR29cH7Y9Gn72jBSuFmUKnnqDNs=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipOohRR2oiy_AFVVHu1Esz2qsLVBAw5HzA_MVyKv=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNNgALOgLWZs1rsnoIQM1xLVI54PgzkvqGrloVe=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]<//pics>< response>

Omg.... we are so full and happy. We decided to get the Baja bucket for 2 with a side cluster of snow crab and a Pineapple Margherita. Such a great idea. There were 6 small lobster tails, so many shrimp we didn't know if we could eat it all (oh, but we did).  The corn and the sides were so good too.  We ate almost everything,  leaving behind a small bit of the skirt steak and chicken. Not because it wasn't cooked perfectly,  just because we ate way too many chips and Salas before the meal arrived. They ar slightly seasoned and so addictive. I'd say go here soon. It's not a cheap date, but so worth every penny spent. Yum.<//Review>

Just off the main strip of old town San Diego. Decent prices, food is super good though and the lobster tacos are real spiny lobster and not longastino. The decor is relaxed Baja inspired and the running fountain in the main dining area is relaxing. Oh and the lobster bites were amazing, and even though it was an appetizer, it could totally be a meal by itself with the fries it comes with.< /review>

< review>
I had made reservations a couple days prior to going online. As we walk up we see that the entrance is is roped off to two sections on top it says ‚Äúenter‚Äù and ‚Äúexit‚Äù there are people standing around waiting on both sides. So we stand on the side that says enter, did not know that was the stand by side. The other side is for people to wait who have reservations. (We didn‚Äôt find this out till after we were waiting in line and just watching other people go in). It was difficult to get someone to even answer the question, ‚ÄúWhere do we stand if we have a reservation?‚Äù There was a woman of color waiting on the reservation side thinking she was suppose to wait there to be seated as a walk up. She had been waiting longer than us, they told her she had to be in the other line by then the walk up line had grown and she had to go all the way to the back. We told her not to wait in the back and she could go ahead of us. She was really thankful. Point being, all the confusion could be avoided if there was a clear sign that says walk up and reservations.
The food was good, portions are a good size as well. I got a margarita and it was more ice than anything. The service inside was good. I get it you get the Baja experience without having to cross the border, I just personally think there are better sea food places in San Diego.<//review>

Outside ambience with heated lamps and overtones of waterfall melodies was quite a delightful atmosphere given the confusion of lawmakers and restaurants. Reservations are highly recommended although walk-ins are accepted. You will likely be waiting if arriving 3 pm or later on a Saturday.

We stayed a couple of hours because girl time is necessary during these times. Although not on the menu, order a ü••+ üçç margarita on the rocks with Don Julio.

< Review>
We had been at Sea World for the day and one of our party wanted lobster so we headed to this restaurant. Our seating outside was nice and the waiter was attentive. I seldom drink, but a maragarita sounded so good so I ordered one on ice with salt. I drank enough to see that the class was totally full of ice. At that point you could not tip the class or the ice would fall on your face. I didn't complain, but my daughter as to see someone about the drink. A man came, which later was told it was the manager, and he said that he had been making this drink for 40 years and that this is how he always does it. He said that is the only way you don't taste the alcohol.? He asked me if I wanted a straw to reach the remaining drink. At that point my daughter told him to take it back and don't charge us. He then commented I should not have drank it if I had a problem. Shaming me into looking like I just wanted a free drink. I know we were sun burned and had park clothes so I felt he was degrading to me and to my daughter (I am in my 70's). I asked my friend on FB and they agreed this was not right. He could have taken out some ice and put in some more mix and taken care of the problem. We had all ordered food and we did tip our waiter well. His treatment of me was degrading.</Review>

< review>
Amidst the global pandemic this place has pumped up their overall cost of your bill by 4% to account for a list of reasons why the company cannot pay its employees the wage or the benefits they deserve. This information is provided on a small laminated placard at the hostess stand. As a result, YOU, the patron, will pay the difference to make up for the business‚Äôs shortcomings. If everyone‚Äôs paycheck reflected the 4% inflated cost of living this might make sense. Problematically, what this really says is ‚ÄúWe know we haven‚Äôt been paying our employees a livable wage. We still can‚Äôt. Here, you do it instead.‚Äù It‚Äôs arguable that supplies (gloves, hand sanitizer, barriers, etc.) have been implemented as mandatory to keep business operating. However, that is what overhead is for. As a capitalist, your lackluster budgeting is putting you in the position to take from where you should be giving. You‚Äôve earned this one.

Congratulations, your capitalism will be your demise and you will only have yourself to blame. :)< /review>

<user>113005512761413384800</user><name>Paul Kendrick<//name><text>This was not my first visit to this restaurant.  My last visit was over 10yrs ago.  A lot has changed since then.  The scenery and ambiance is similar to what I remember.  However, the food is not.  We started off with the Calamari.  It was cooked nicely, not over battered.  The sauce they poured over it was a sweet chili style, which was unusual, but good.  Next we all ordered tacos.  I had the Tres Amigos with everything.  The mixture of steak and shrimp was well done.  I didn't care for the nacho cheese they poured over it.  It really overpowered the taste of meat.  I wished I would have asked for hard shell, instead of the soft tortillas.  The rice and beans were just okay to me.  Nothing to write home about.  The others in my group had the fish tacos, the ahi tacos, and carne asada tacos.  The Ahi was amazing.  The fish taco was okay.  The carne asada was okay.  Lastly, we had the fried ice cream.  That was a pleasant surprise.  It was just enough for the 3 of us to enjoy it. Over all the meal was okay.  Next time I will order what they are known for, Lobster.</text><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< Date>

<userid>111041117256767092830< /userid><user_name>Josepina F. Martinez< /user_name>< time>
1622480595746<//time>
<rating>2<//rating>< Review>
Salty food, red pork enchiladas were horrible, Margaritas served in a cheap plastic cup, tasted like they use cheap wine to make them instead of Tequila. I thought I was in Tijuana. Half of the chips were super salty dusted with a red powder on them. The regular iced tea tastes like a combination of their raspberry iced tea and regular iced tea. I returned the Margarita and my pork enchiladas. I settled for a selected few chips and salsa brought to our table and a bowl of the Lobster Corn Chowder which wasnt bad.
At the end, I asked the server why we were being charged a surcharge she calls Manager over. A tall raspy-speaking guy came to our table and proceeded to explain the reason for the surcharge. Basically what I got is he prefers to charge this surcharge instead of raising the prices due to the  minimum wage now being $15 an hour. When I advised him it wouldve been nice to be told up front he gave me a very matter of fact look and replied "ITS ON THE MENU.." Forgive me for not looking for a surcharge in a not-so-well-lit restaurant when I'm trying to figure out what sounds appealing for me for dinner, I thought to myself then I replied "ok". But the whole time thinking IM NEVER COMING BACK HERE".

The whole time I sat there, I was highly aware of the close proximity to vehicles buzzing and speeding by about 20 to 25 feet away just over a horizontal wooden fence. I could see the headlights in between the wood planks and at times the noise was deafening especially if a HOG went by.

The prices were not necessarily expensive. however,  I dont mind paying more for good food and good spirits.

The wait in line for 3 people was not bad. The speed and accuracy of the servers was good.

I love road trips. Over the last couple years I've noticed a decline in excellent customer service.<//Review>

Although Google said 'Dine-In was Allowed' (post Covid-19 Reopening) Sadly we discovered that Dine-In was for 'Patio Seating' Only!
(Despite most other restaurants in Old Town having full Dine-In seating available!!)
...And then we noticed that there was actually vacant Patio seating available before, during, & past our Reservation time. -So why weren't we being seated !?
Our patio seating was NOT covered by an overhead awning, and there was burnt ash particles (from an earlier San Diego fire) that was snowing down all over our open-air table.
Additionally, there were swarms of black fly's buzzing around our table, because the tables were not properly cleaned from the previous guests,
We were forced to sit at this Ash-Covered, Fly-Infested Nightmare for another 10-Min's, while the waitstaff totally ignored us,
My Son had to get up and interrupt a group of idle-handed waitress' to ask them to bring us some silverware & menu's.
The silverware arrived -but the menus did not !
We weren't informed by waitstaff that we'd need to download a QR code reader App to scan their 3-D dot code menu's to our phones.

<Text>We are (no, we were) old Rockin' Baja Lobster customers. We ordered the lobster deal for two. Worst crab fish, yes, too small to call them lobster tails. Also, they were too salty to be edible and slight on the burned side. The beefsteak tasted funny, almost like a soybean steak. They included now the smallest flour tortillas they have ever provided. The chip had a hint of being fried in (recycled?) fish oil, we say that because the chips had a strong taste of fish.

Reluctantly, we are giving them one star because the shrimp were large but, unfortunately, also very salty. And, because the chard chicken was the only good thing on our plate.

This is our last visit to Rockin' Lobster in Old Town. We longer can recommend them.< /Text><pics>None</pics><Resp>None</Resp>< Gmap_id>

< text>
This spot is legit. üëå Great food & great service! It's walking distance in Old Town with a free lot nearby. This came with rice & beans that I hardly touched bc this bucket was so filling. I opted to upgrade the corn to the Mexican street corn that is made just like an elote on the cob. They also have a free chip & salsa bar where the chips are under a heat lamp. They provide little containers for different salsas, extra lemons, bean salads etc.. huge variety. I highly recommend the pineapple mango salsa. It was.. probably the best thing I've ever had. I ate it with the chips & also added it to my crab, lobster & shrimp tacos. Oh! Forgot to mention they give you warm tortillas üòã the Margarita was pretty good too. The live music was super fun.
Overall.. this is definitely a spot worth trying. You will not regret it.
When I'm back in San Diego in a few months, I'll definitely be back.< /text>

Would go again, but only if in the area or with someone else paying. Not worth the money.</review>

< UserId.>
114542560508325625280<//UserId.>
<Rating>5</Rating>< Review>
We love this place, I wish it was back here in Arizona. The prices are up there but we feel the atmosphere made it worth always coming back to.

They have a salsa bar with quite the variety where you can help yourself. The dinner plates are HUGE and I had to take home half of my plate so be warned. The drinks are a bit much, it was $12 for a glass here compared to the same size at other places we frequent but you can always order the special, which seemed to be around $6-$8.

I can't tell you the food is amazing because I usually eat a ton of salsa then only have a burrito. But I can tell you that they added vegan/veterinarian options which was the main reason we wanted to come back in the first place. You can get the beyond meat with nearly anything instead of actual meat. The down side is, it costs way more to do so. If a veggie burrito was $14, chicken would be $15, seafood $16, red meat $17, Beyond Beef ("fake" meat) $18. The burrito took me 2 dinners to eat it all but my husband ate it in one sitting. Anyways, be prepared to pay more than your typical restaurant.< /Review>

<text>My wife and I brought friends from out of town here on Friday night. It was honestly a huge miscalculation, because one of the three kids with us is autistic, and he's a bit sound sensitive. Shortly after we arrived, the live band was playing, and it got kind of loud, on top of being a busy restaurant. My heart sank, and we were totally prepared to bail if our friend couldn't handle it.

He actually had a great time! It turns out that he was recently starting to enjoy music, and he started grooving along to the band. Our server Shawn was great as well. Super attentive, and really nice to the kids, making them feel like part of the situation.

There was a really nice woman walking around taking photos, but unfortunately I didn't catch her name. She snapped photos of our group, and came back shortly with prints. I was prepared to buy them no matter how they turned out.

The photos are freaking excellent. Really nice prints in San Diego themed frames, professional composition and lighting or whatever photographers say when things turn out just right. We are so happy to have that night captured for us to remember. Seriously, she did a great job.

Thanks so much for helping us have a really special, memorable night.</text>< UserId.>

< review>
Went here with my daughter,  brother,  and mom (it was my bro's 50th birthday). We  weren't aware that you could sign up online prior to your birthday to get a baja bucket. I split the Baja Bucket with my 15 year olds daughter. It comes with Rock lobster(MY FAVE), shrimp, chicken, carne asada steak cutlets, tortillas,  rice, and beans. ALSO unlimited salsa bar and very yummy authentic tortilla chips. Perfect for 2 people. We have pretty good appetites and still had a couple shrimp left over.  We sat right near the indoor waterfall which was s nice touch. Parking lot was full but I managed to squeeze into a non-working spot, lol. I'm a rebel that way because I'm impatient and I'd be darned if I was gonna pay $5 to park in the adjoining lot. It's not a romantic place. It's busy. Seating is courtyard style but no complaints. Good vibes. Good drinks. Good food...<//review>

<rating>4<//rating><review>Pretty good Mexican restaurant in San Diego. This place is right on the edge of Old Town, and the food here is decent. They have a self serve chip and salsa bar, which I like. Our server was friendly and helpful, although the seating process was a rock rocky. The prices were a bit high, but it is a tourist area, and they do include an automatic 3% gratuity on top of what you tip. The portions are pretty huge; we stuffed ourselves and took some home. They also have a person taking photos and selling the prints, which adds to the touristy element. However, they really didn't try to force that on you. < Review>
Great food with a fun atmosphere and happy staff.  A casual setting with both indoor and outdoor seating and live music on the weekends.  I love this place and their food... lots and lots of seafood choices.   It's a great alternative to other more traditional Mexican restaurants in old town San Diego. Insider tip: this is a great spot for happy hour or dinner if you're from out of town.  They have a large menu,  big dishes and fun seafood buckets that you can share. Tacos are excellent here especially the shrimp and lobster tacos!</Review>

<text>You would think that with the word "lobster" actually in the name of the restaurant that they would know how to cook lobster well.  Not so! I had the Maine Lobster roll and it was dry, chewy, overcooked and it totally lacked the signature sweetness that you expect from real Maine lobster.  This seemed to have some sort of blend of langostino meat, CA spiny lobster and "maybe" some Maine.  Maybe...  Regardless of what is actually in it, there is no excusing how poorly it was prepared.  Lacking that, consider this just a run of the mill Mexican restaurant.</text>< pictures>

< Review>
Unfortunately, our dinner experience was no where near what we were expecting. We decided to take our family that was visiting from out of town for a fun/nice dinner and didn't have the best experience right from the start. We arrived at 4:30 pm and there was no one waiting so we walked right up to the hostess stand and let her know we had a party of 5. She proceeded to ask us is we minded a tall table. We let her know that would be fine and she asked us to give her a couple of minutes. The hostess seemed to be more concerned about socializing with staff and seemed to forget that we were sitting right in front of her waiting. After around 15 minutes of waiting, two ladies walked up, were asked if they minded a tall table, and they were immediately taken to be seated. I then took it apon myself to take a peak in the restaurant where there were open tables everywhere. So I walked back to the hostess stand and spoke with another hostess which could not locate our name written down anywhere. She apologized, took us to the bar seating area, and sat us next to the women that came in 15 minutes after us (they were at the same side table as us). After this, we were happy to have a nice server but still upset about the unnecessary wait. On the way out, we stopped at the hostess stand and asked for a few wet naps as we ordered the ribs, and she told us it would take a few minutes. We declined and left the restaurant pretty surprised with the service. I have worked in the restaurant business for years and could never imagine treating guests in this way. This was such a bummer!!</Review>

<review>Unfortunately, our dinner experience was no where near what we were expecting. We decided to take our family that was visiting from out of town for a fun/nice dinner and didn't have the best experience right from the start. We arrived at 4:30 pm and there was no one waiting so we walked right up to the hostess stand and let her know we had a party of 5. She proceeded to ask us is we minded a tall table. We let her know that would be fine and she asked us to give her a couple of minutes. The hostess seemed to be more concerned about socializing with staff and seemed to forget that we were sitting right in front of her waiting. After around 15 minutes of waiting, two ladies walked up, were asked if they minded a tall table, and they were immediately taken to be seated. I then took it apon myself to take a peak in the restaurant where there were open tables everywhere. So I walked back to the hostess stand and spoke with another hostess which could not locate our name written down anywhere. She apologized, took us to the bar seating area, and sat us next to the women that came in 15 minutes after us (they were at the same side table as us). After this, we were happy to have a nice server but still upset about the unnecessary wait. On the way out, we stopped at the hostess stand and asked for a few wet naps as we ordered the ribs, and she told us it would take a few minutes. We declined and left the restaurant pretty surprised with the service. I have worked in the restaurant business for years and could never imagine treating guests in this way. This was such a bummer!!</review>< pics>

< Text>
This place exceeded my expectations, which were high based on a friend's recommendation.  If you like crab and lobster, get the Cortez bucket.  With all the sides, one bucket is enough for two.  The snow crab, especially, is better than any I've had elsewhere - thick, juicy chunks and seasoned so they are delicious with or without drawn butter.  Overall one of the best seafood restaurants I've ever been to.  We'll be back again!<//Text>

< Review>
Very disappointing. Contrary to what other reviewers have posted, no chips and salsa were offered. Margaritas lacked flavor. Lobster Lovers' combo included a deep-fried lobster taco, which was quite good, but the few chunks of langosta in the small enchilada were overwhelmed by the cheese. To top it off, everything was overpriced. On the plus side, my server Nicole was very friendly and helpful. With so many great Mexican restaurants in San Diego this one is best avoided.<//Review>

Well well well...
No, all the buzz and a lot of noise but no true flavors. Lobster roll? If anything, at a mid range perfection. I can here because some friends told me about it. Nah, such friend I have that they have no sense of flavor nor what a great atmosphere feels like!
Anyways, the service was okay too, and for that I won't complain since I know the shortage of labor.
Carnitas tacos are good though!
I gotta say however, they have some funny quotes out here !</Text>
